FBIS4-33698 "drlat112_b_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-112 Daily Report 9 Jun 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti Foreign Nationals Could Begin Leaving Foreign Nationals Could Begin Leaving FL0906184394 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1045 GMT 9 Jun 94 FL0906184394 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole French BFN [Text] Sources close to some of the diplomatic missions in Port-au-Prince are reporting that some foreign nationals have allegedly begun leaving the country in light of a possible armed intervention. Members of international and nongovernmental organizations working in the country could start leaving on 10 June on the recommendation of their respective countries. Some meetings have been held on this issue, but no public notice has been issued yet.
